.TH "URL" 7 "February 2026" "atomdns handlers" "atomdns authors"

.SH "NAME"
.PP
\fIurl\fP \- serve zone data from an URL

.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.PP
The \fIurl\fP handler is used for serving zone data that is fetched from an URL. The most prominent example of
this is downloading the root zone from https://www.internic.net/domain/root.zone
\[la]https://www.internic.net/domain/root.zone\[ra].

.PP
The server will reply with minimal responses by default. The \fIurl\fP handler will watch the zone file and when
it receives a (kernel) notify it will reload the zone after 2 seconds.

.SH "SYNTAX"
.PP
.RS

.nf
url FILE {
    URL
}

.fi
.RE

.IP \(bu 4
\fBFILE\fP the zone file to save the data to and to serve from. If the path is relative, the path from the
global root config will be prepended to it.
.IP \(bu 4
\fBURL\fP the URL to fetch the zone from, a scheme must be used. This may be used multiple times, in which
subsequent URLs are used as backup and downloaded when the earlier URL doesn't work.


.PP
If the handler block specification contains multiple zones, they all will use the \fIsame\fP \fBFILE\fP. And you must make
sure that zone \fBFILE\fP is generic enough, i.e. use \fB\fC@\fR for zones instead of domain names.

.SH "EXAMPLES"
.PP
Load the root zone from and save it in \fB\fCroot.transferred\fR.

.PP
.RS

.nf
\&. {
    url root.transferred {
        https://www.internic.net/domain/root.zone
    }
}

.fi
.RE
